By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –   The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control  in its latest COVID-19 report said it has confirmed 356 new infections, bringing the total confirmed cases to 78,790. The report released via the agency’s twitter handle also informed that 68,483 persons who earlier tested positive for COVID-19 have been treated, recovered and discharged from various isolation facilities across the country. It added regrettably that 1,227 COVID-19 related deaths have been recorded in Nigeria so far. The report listed the states where the new infections were recorded and numbers as follows: FCT-79Lagos-59Kaduna-56Katsina-37Nasarawa-30Kano-25Edo-18Gombe-14Kebbi-12Akwa Ibom-7Rivers-7Sokoto-7Abia-3Ogun-1Cross River -1 It also gave the breakdown of total confirmed cases thus: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest COVID-19 report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has it that 152 new cases were confirmed on Sunday bringing the total confirmed cases to 65,148. It also said that 61,073 patients have been discharged since the index case was… November 16, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Thursday said that it has confirmed 354 new cases of COVID-19 infection, bringing the total confirmed cases to 45,244. The health agency reported that the 354 new infections were recorded in 17 out of the 36… August 7, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 patients hit 48,770 in Nigeria as another 325 persons tested positive to the novel virus on Saturday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. In the report released late Saturday, the agency said the 325 cases… August 16, 2020 In "News"